Fabric skill: open-code-review

This skill is a derivative adaptation of:

  open-code-review — https://github.com/alibaba/open-code-review
  Copyright the open-code-review authors.
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

What was reused: the review methodology (deterministic file selection, rule
resolution, delegated per-file review) and the structured finding schema
(path, content, start/end line, suggestion_code, existing_code). The `category`
and `severity` gradings are Fabric additions, not upstream fields.

What was changed: reimplemented natively for Fabric using local `git` and the
`delegate_task` primitive. The upstream `ocr` Go binary is NOT used, and its
`internal/telemetry` (OpenTelemetry) integration is therefore absent — this
adaptation contacts no telemetry or reporting endpoint.

